This is an original, handcrafted pin signed by the artist, Linda Rosshirt (me). The porcelain-look resin face is already painted and I embellish to create the pin’s own distinct look. As I add hats, hair, jewelry and/or fur, each pin develops her own personality that I try to convey in the finished piece. Great attention is given to detail to make each pin a unique work. These pins wear as well with your favorite faded jeans as they do your Sunday best. I like to dress them up with exotic, romantic or mod looks and wear the one that best fits my mood. So, add a dash of panache to a coat, dress or blouse. Dress up a jacket, brighten a vest and lift your spirits! I hope you have as much fun wearing as I do creating them. This pin’s individual attributes are: Type of face: full face view Approximate size of pin: 1 3/4" L x 1 1/4" W Main colors used: purple, pink, green Description: Her blue eyes are accented with black eyeliner and light purple eye shadow and her lips are bright red. She is a harbinger of Spring, wearing a deeply-cuffed purple hat with a cluster of tiny pin, purple and yellow clay flowers at the side. The matching earrings are pale purple glass beads with little flecks of gold fused in. They measure approximately 1 1/2" long from the top of the gold tone ear wires.
